<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-17T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-17T03:00:00-05:00" n="689" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d689">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/797: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iraq</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Satterthwaite</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Baghdad</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-17T11:00:00+03:00">July 17, 1937—11
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received July 17—7:32 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>19. My 18, July 13, 1 p.m.<note n="21" xml:id="d689fn21">Not
                                    printed.</note> Iraq Government appears to be taking lead in
                                opposition to Palestine partition scheme and yesterday afternoon <pb facs="0906" n="895" xml:id="pg_895"/> permitted large public
                                demonstration, committee of which has telegraphed Legation
                                requesting support of the United States Government. Official and
                                popular resentment against Emir Abdula [<hi rend="italic">Abdullah</hi>] reported increasing.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Satterthwaite</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>